Tamasheq: Turkiya tla aǧăriw deɣ krad iɣilan: ejarew wan Aegean deɣ amǝneǧ, Black Sea deɣ afella d ejarew wan Mediterane deɣ aǧus. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Tamasheq: Daɣ ănemmănɣi tămeɣan fal aman andukan ɣas beccan as I yussa radar yunayer, tuǧaǧen daw amăn full inin icenga cwaden d-sen. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Tamasheq: Issunfa daɣ tăkerkurt n idraren win ăfella n Mekka, ǝkahhăm ǝlla daɣ aǧilăl ful eddunet ɣăred. 
English: The city of Mekka is surrounded by a wall, and the gates are guarded by soldiers.

Tamasheq: Daɣ aǧilăl n tăkert n idraren n Mekka, aǧilăl n tăkert n idraren n ġayr n ġayr n ġayr n ġayr n ġayr n ġayr n ġayr n ġay
